\documentclass[11pt]{article}
\usepackage[margin=1in]{geometry}
\usepackage[hidelinks]{hyperref}
\pagenumbering{gobble}
\setlength{\parskip}{0.65em}
\begin{document}

\noindent Date: March 16, 2026

\vspace{10pt}
Hiring Manager \\
Relativity Space \\

\vspace{10pt}
Dear Hiring Manager,

The role of Simulation Software Engineer I at Relativity Space offers me the chance to work directly on the construction of the Terran R vehicle, which represents the innovative technology that Relativity Space is known for. I admire how this company is using cutting-edge technology with innovative problem-solving to change how aerospace companies manufacture and launch their products. My background in simulation software development and GNC algorithms gives me a solid foundation to make valuable contributions to optimizing the flight characteristics of the Terran R vehicle, both from conception to flight operations. I have significant experience in leading a team to develop high-fidelity six degrees-of-freedom (6DOF) simulation models to improve aerospace applications’ prediction accuracy by 20\textbackslash{}\%. This prior experience would be directly applicable to the responsibilities of the Simulation Engineer I at Relativity Space as I develop and integrate subsystem models into the 6DOF simulations performed. Furthermore, the completion of Hardware-in-the-Loop testing improved our testing validation process and reduced our overall testing time by 30\textbackslash{}\%, demonstrating my ability to create efficiencies through innovative methods. I am proficient in the programming languages of C++, Rust and Python that will assist me in addressing the complex simulation issues that you are facing, especially in the areas of developing numerical solvers and physics models. My first focus would be to integrate the subsystem model into an existing 6DOF simulation and develop workflow efficiencies for our GNC algorithm development. I am excited to become a member of the team that is leading the aerospace industry in innovation by adding my simulation expertise and collaborative work ethic.

Sincerely, \\
Sri Akash Kadali \\
kadali18@umd.edu \\
+1 240-726-9356

\end{document}
